<DOC><DOCNO> ZF32-054-039 </DOCNO><DOCID>11 316 387</DOCID><JOURNAL>MacWEEK  Sept 24 1991 v5 n32 p18(1)* Full Text COPYRIGHT Coastal Associates Publishing L.P. 1991.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>MacX25 switches to System 7.0. (Apple MacX25 1.0.1 computernetwork software) (brief article) (product announcement)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Wylie, Margie.andM;</AUTHOR><DESCRIPT>Company:   Apple Computer Inc. (Product introduction).andO;Ticker:    AAPL.andO;Product:   MacX25 1.0.1 (Computer network software) (Product introduction)System 7.0 (Operating system) (Usage).andO;Topic:     Network SoftwareConnectivityLocal Area NetworksEnhancementsApple Dealers AssociationProduct Introduction.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>By Margie WylieandM;Cupertino, Calif.andP;  -- System 7.0 users now can use relatively inexpensivepacket-switched network connections since Apple last week upgraded its MacX25gateway.andM;Now available through APDA, the $800 MacX25 1.0.1 is a slightly improved andSystem 7-savvy upgrade to the company's X.25 gateway software and client.andM;Based on the CCITT X.25 standard for packet-switched networks, MacX25 letsMacs on an AppleTalk network access X.25 networks without buying a PAD(packet assembler disassembler), an expensive hardware component normallyused to connect to packet-switched networks.andM;Instead, MacX25 uses a Mac II-series computer as a gateway between X.25wide-area services and networked Macs.andP;  Connected to the packet-switchednetwork through Apple's serial card, the server provides X.25 connections tonetworked Macs running the MacPAD client software.andM;Under MacX25 1.0.1, MacPAD is implemented as a connection tool for theMacintosh Communications Toolbox.andP;  As a result, developers can incorporateMacX25's services into applications that work with the CommunicationsToolbox.andM;For example, by supporting the Comm Toolbox and using MacX25's ProgrammingLibrary to negotiate connections through the gateway, a terminal emulator orsoftware router maker could add X.25 services to its product.andP;  The MacX25Programming Library, available separately, remains unchanged.andM;For international users who count on X.25 for wide-area connections, MacX25also supports European character sets, such as the umlat or tilde.andM;The MacX25 1.0.1 server requires 4 Mbytes of memory under System 7.0 and 2Mbytes under System 6.0.7.andP;  MacPAD requires 2 Mbytes under System 7.0 and 1Mbyte under System 6.0.7.andM;APDA can be reached at (408) 562-3910 or (800) 282-2732 in the United States,and (800) 637-0029 in Canada.andO;</TEXT></DOC>